methods.threadDump:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Generate a thread dump as a String.

*Overload 1*  
  :param out: (java.io.PrintStream) - the output stream to write the thread dump of the current process to
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param logger: (io.deephaven.io.logger.Logger) - the logger to write the thread dump of the current process to
  
*Overload 3*  
  :return: (java.lang.String) a String containing a thread dump of the curent process.

text:
A simple method for generating a Thread dump for this JVM; it doesn't do all the stuff that the kill -3 does; but you
 can easily run it from inside the JVM without having to send yourself a signal.
